p: Overall, the composition was dominated by Terpenenoid compounds with 64.9%, followed by Aliphatic Acids (7%) and Aliphatic Alkanes (2.9%). The most abundant compounds (> 4.0%) were phytol (29.6%; Fig 1), neophytadiene (6.6%) with its isomer III (4.6%), hexadecanoic acid (5.5%), 3-(2,6,6-Trimethyl-1-cyclohexen-1-yl)-2-propenal (5.5%) and isophytol (4.6%), contributing together 56.4% of the total composition accounting to 80.3%.
